  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Understand the polynomial representation and derivative rule",
      "atomics": [
        "Identify that xs[i] is the coefficient of x^i, so the polynomial is sum(xs[i]*x^i for i in 0..n-1)",
        "Apply the power rule: derivative of xs[i]*x^i is i*xs[i]*x^(i-1), contributing coefficient i*xs[i] to the output at index i-1",
        "Note that the constant term xs[0] vanishes and the output list is one element shorter than the input"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Construct the output coefficient list",
      "atomics": [
        "Iterate over indices i from 1 to len(xs)-1",
